# JavaScript DOM

- DOM stands for document object model
- the whole document of a website and its all elements are called DOM elements
- We can add remove, change, and even delete elements from DOM
- DOM operation are executed by DOM event
- DOM properties and methods help DOM manipulation
- DOM object is a document

# DOM Object

- title
- domain
- images
- doctype
- head
- body
- url
- links
- scripts
- forms
- embeds
- cookies

# DOM Selectors - ok

- getElementById()
- getElementsByClassName()
- getElementsByTagName()
- querySelector()
- querySelectorAll()

# DOM Property and Methods

- innerHTML
- innerText
- textContent
- setAttribute()
- getAttribute()
- hasAttribute()
- style
- className
- classList.add()
- classList.remove()
- classList.replace()
- classList.toggle()
- classList.contains()
- id
- children
- firstChild / firstElementChild
- lastChild / lastElementChild
- parentElement
- nextElementSibling
- previousElementSibling
- value

# Add and Delete Elements

